9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 630, L.D. 970, “An Act to Prioritize
10 Affordable Housing by Expediting Reviews for Affordable Housing Projects Applying for
11 Funding from the Maine State Housing Authority”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Support Affordable Housing Development'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
15 following:
16 'Sec. 1. 38 MRSA §488, sub-§30 is enacted to read:
17 30. Exemption for construction of new dwelling units at existing development.
18 New construction of dwelling units at an existing development that has been permitted
19 pursuant to this article is exempt from review under this article if:
20 A. The additional disturbed area not to be revegetated does not exceed 40,000 square
21 feet ground area in any calendar year and does not exceed 80,000 square feet ground
22 area in total;
23 B. Any new dwelling units to be constructed that are designed to accommodate more
24 than 4 families are connected to a public water and sewer system;
25 C. The new construction is not contrary to the terms or conditions of the permit, other
26 than by the addition of new disturbed area for dwelling units. An area designated by
27 the permit for storm water management or for natural resource or visual buffers may
28 not be developed under this exemption. Subsurface wastewater disposal systems or
29 wells may not be constructed in an area excluded by the permit for the placement of
30 those systems; and
31 D. The permittee annually notifies the department of any new construction conducted
32 during the previous 12 months that is eligible for the exemption under this subsection.
33 The notice must identify the type, location and ground area of the new construction.
34 With the annual notification, the permittee shall provide to the department development
